
                             Highway Hunter v1.0

=============================================================================
                    * Instructions/Troubleshooting Info *
=============================================================================


System Requirements
===================

  ţ Fast 386 or better CPU
  ţ 570K free RAM
  ţ 2 Megs HD space
  ţ VGA card and monitor

Recommended hardware:

  ţ Joystick or Mouse
  ţ Sound Blaster


To start Highway Hunter
=======================

1. Switch to the drive where the game is installed (C:)
2. Switch to the subdirectory where the game is installed (CD \HH)
3. Type "Start"


=============================================================================

                            Playing the Game

=============================================================================


 Keyboard Commands
 =================

     ARROW keys move your vehicle around.

      CTRL keys fire your current weapon.

         P pauses the game.

       ESC Quits the game.


 Joystick Configuration
 ======================

     If you want to use Highway Hunter with a joystick, you need
     to select JOYSTICK SETUP from the Main Menu, then follow
     the instructions given.


 Upgrade Modules
 ===============

     During the game, try to collect upgrade modules that come your
     way by running into them with your vehicle. Each type of module
     serves a special purpose that will increase your chances of
     completing the game.


    UPGRADE     PURPOSE

       C    =   Executes a massive photon pulse that does damage to
                all of the enemies on the screen.

       O    =   Gives you temporary invincibility.

       U    =   Gives you more weapon units. If you exceed the weapon
                units for your current weapon, your vehicle will be
                upgraded to the next available weapon type.

 WEAPONS
 =======

   Highway Hunter has 9 available weapons. As you find weapon upgrades,
   your current weapon increases in power. If you exceed the amount of
   power your current weapon can handle, your weapon will be upgraded to
   the next available weapon. Weapon upgrades require a lot of energy.
   This energy is depleted as it is used. If your upgrade runs out of
   energy, your weapons system will revert back to the next lower weapon.


 SHIELDS
 =======

    Shield upgrades are also available during the game. For a limited time,
    they will protect your vehicle from mines and oncoming enemy attack. You
    obtain different shields by running your vehicle over shield modules on
    the highway. Each shield type serves a different purpose and a different
    method of helping you. Hint: After you understand how different shields
    work, try to select of the type of shield best suited to your play style.



=============================================================================

                            Troubleshooting

=============================================================================


 NOT ENOUGH FREE MEMORY
 ======================

   If you run Highway Hunter, and the game refuses to start and gives
   me the message "You need (amount) of free memory to run this program",
   you need to free up more main (conventional) memory.

   Here are some solutions:

1. If you are trying to run Highway Hunter from Windows, completely exit
   Windows and try running it from DOS.

2. If you are trying to run Highway Hunter from "DOSSHELL" or any other
   menu program,  please exit from the menu program.  Then, run Highway
   Hunter from the DOS prompt.  Menu programs often occupy enough memory
   that there won't be enough left for Highway Hunter.

If neither #1 or #2 solves the problem,  do the following:

1. From the DOS prompt,  type "MEM" and press Enter.

2. You'll see a lot of information about your computer's memory.  Look at
   the number after the words "Largest Executable Program Size".  This is
   the amount of memory you currently have available.

Now you need to free up more main memory.  Here are some tips:


1. You may need to modify your AUTOEXEC.BAT and CONFIG.SYS files
   in your root directory.  This can be done in any version of DOS.

   Rewrite your CONFIG.SYS file to contain the lines:

           HIMEM.SYS
           EMM386.EXE NOEMS HIGHSCAN
           DOS=HIGH,UMB

2. We also recommend that you clean out all other TSR's and memory
   managers from CONFIG.SYS by either removing the line, or by typing
   "REM" before the command.

3. Once your CONFIG.SYS and AUTOEXEC.BAT files have been changed, you must
   restart your computer for the changes to take effect. Do this by
   pressing the CTRL-ALT-DEL keys simultaneously.

4. A handy program for MS-DOS 6.0+ users is MEMMAKER.  This file will
   help you optimize your CONFIG.SYS and AUTOEXEC.BAT files to allow
   you optimal memory conservation.

5. Please read the manual that came with DOS for more information about
   configuring memory.



 SOUND
 =====
    
    Highway Hunter was designed to work with Sound Blaster and
    100% compatible sound cards. 

    The first time you run Highway Hunter, you will be asked to configure
    your sound card. After you choose the type of sound card you have, 
    the setup program will ask you for specific information regarding
    your sound card. If the SET BLASTER environment is found, Highway
    Hunter will read the needed information from this command. Otherwise,
    the port address, IRQ, and DMA channel must be entered manually.
    Consult the manual that came with your sound card for further
    details on the SET BLASTER command and sound card configuration.


 RUNNING UNDER Windows OR OS/2
 =============================

    This game should work properly under Windows and OS/2 if you turn all
    sound card support OFF when configuring the game.  However, if you want
    to hear music or sound through your Sound Blaster card, you must run
    Highway Hunter through DOS.

More Windows and OS/2 tips:

1. Even though Highway Hunter will work under Windows with sound card
   support turned OFF,  the graphics will run more smoothly under plain DOS.

2. If you try to run Highway Hunter through Windows or OS/2 with sound card
   support ON,  you'll get unpredictable results - Highway Hunter will not
   run properly.

3. If you encounter any problems running through Windows or OS/2, exit and
   run Highway Hunter through plain DOS instead!  This will likely solve any
   problems you are encountering.

4. Running Highway Hunter through the "MS-DOS Shell" in Windows (or the
   OS/2 DOS box) is NOT the same as running it straight from DOS.  For
   best results, you need to completely exit from Windows or OS/2 and run
   Highway Hunter from the DOS prompt.




 Game Speed
 ==========

   If you find that Highway Hunter runs too fast on your computer, change
   the SPEED setting in the main menu of the game to a lower speed.


